+ User Authentication

++ Set up a minimal authentication source

<code type="bash">
$ htpasswd -c -s /var/www/conf/htpasswd.conf username
New password: 
Re-type new password: 
Adding password for user username
</code>

++ Edit Solar.config.php to point to the authentication source

<code type="bash">
$ vi Solar.config.php
$ 
</code>

<code type="php">
$config = array();

// SQL connection
$config['Solar_Sql'] = array(
	'class' => 'Solar_Sql_Driver_Mysql',
	'host'  => '127.0.0.1',
	'user'  => 'username',
	'pass'  => 'password',
	'name'  => 'database',
);

// Front controller HREF prefix
$config['Solar_Uri']['action'] = '/index.php';

// Public directory HREF prefix
$config['Solar_Uri']['public'] = '/public';

// Authentication source
$config['Solar_User']['auth']['class'] = 'Solar_User_Auth_Htpasswd';
$config['Solar_User']['auth']['options']['file'] = '/var/www/conf/htpasswd.conf';

// Done!
return $config;
</code>

++ Browse to "Hello World"

http://example.com/index.php/hello

Attempt to log in with your username and password.


